               <msContents>
                  <summary>Psalter.  F<locus target="#1r">fols. 1r, </locus>-177r: <locus target="#68v">68v, </locus>: The midpoint is marked by writing the line in alternating black and red ink. Psalm 151 is the short version. Song of Songs is a very nice copy of the Scholars Edition. Praises of Mary begins on Monday and culmintates on Sunday. F<locus target="#177r">177r, </locus>-178v: Angels Praise Her. F. i v: Lucky and Unlucky Days of the Year, ጽንዕት፡ ወጽንጽንት፡. F. ii r: Top: Prayer for salvation for ክፍለ ማርያም, and for ወለተ ሚካኤል, and for ወለተ ማርያም. Bottom: Notice of Gift of the book from nun ወለተ ማርያም, to ታደለች. F. ii v: Pen trial with a prayer employing a pun on ብዕር, pen and ብር, money: O Lord, save me from the temptation of money (እምፈቲነ ብር), followed by a prayer for salvation for six persons. Throughout the book, the number ፲ marks every tenth line, as though an audit of the strophes were being performed.  <locus target="#157v">157v</locus> and 178v have notes of ownership, ወለተ ኢየሱስ.</summary>
